      "text": "Brah, we need to talk.\n\nYou're $202 over on partying, $168 over on dining out, $82 over on slop, and your checking account is sitting at $46 when it should be at $1,500. Meanwhile you're paying $127.59 in *interest charges* on that Delta card and your subscriptions are double-charged (you got Claude billed THREE times this period, bro).\n\nStop the bleeding: Kill the duplicate subscriptions TODAY. Cut the restaurants and convenience store runs\u2014you're hemorrhaging money on small transactions that add up fast. Your parking alone is almost $50 when your cap is $30.\n\nGet your checking balance back above zero first. Then we fix the rest.\n\nWhat's the move?",
      "date": "2026-07-16"
    },
    {
      "text": "Brah, your situation got *worse*, not better.\n\nYou're still massively over on partying ($202 over cap), dining out ($183 over), and slop ($101 over). Your checking account is now at $161 instead of the $1,500 target. And you're *still* getting charged $127.59 in interest on that Delta card\u2014that's pure waste, bro.\n\nHere's what needs to happen TODAY: Cancel those duplicate Claude subscriptions (you're being billed THREE times). Stop eating out and hitting convenience stores for a week straight. Cut the partying in half minimum. Your parking cap is $30 and you're at $57\u2014walk or bike more.\n\nYou've got $746 in savings. Transfer it to checking, pay down that Delta card to stop the bleeding, then lock in hard limits on wants. You're not broke because you're not earning\u2014you're broke because you're spending like money doesn't exist.\n\nWhat's actually changing this week?",
